  if (n === 1) return 1;
  const dp = Array.from({length: n + 1}, () => [0, 0]);
  dp[0][0] = 1; dp[1][0] = 1;
  for (let i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
    dp[i][0] = dp[i-1][0] + dp[i-1][1];
    dp[i][1] = dp[i-2][0];
  }
  return dp[n][0] + dp[n][1];
}
```

**O(1) space**: only need `dp[i-1]` and `dp[i-2]`, so four scalars suffice.

**Time**: O(n). **Space**: O(1) optimized.

