```javascript
function paytmCoinChangeMin(coins, amount) {
  const INF = Infinity;
  const dp = new Array(amount + 1).fill(INF);
  dp[0] = 0;
  for (let a = 1; a <= amount; a++) {
    for (const c of coins) {
      if (c <= a && dp[a - c] !== INF) {
        dp[a] = Math.min(dp[a], dp[a - c] + 1);
      }
    }
  }
  return dp[amount] === INF ? -1 : dp[amount];
}
```

**Time**: O(amount * |coins|). **Space**: O(amount).

Note: this is the unbounded knapsack form — same coin reusable. Inner loop goes over coins, outer over amounts.

Greedy fail dekho: coins=[1,3,4], amount=6. Greedy 4+1+1=3 coins; DP gives 3+3=2 coins.

