**Key trick**: In a circle, you cannot take both index 0 and index n-1. Split into two non-circular subproblems:
- Case A: ignore index 0; run linear robber on `nums[1..n-1]`.
- Case B: ignore index n-1; run linear robber on `nums[0..n-2]`.
Answer = max(A, B).

```javascript
function houseRobberCircular(nums) {
  const n = nums.length;
  if (n === 1) return nums[0];
  function rob(lo, hi) {
    let prev2 = 0, prev1 = 0;
    for (let i = lo; i <= hi; i++) {
      const cur = Math.max(prev1, prev2 + nums[i]);
      prev2 = prev1; prev1 = cur;
    }
    return prev1;
  }
  return Math.max(rob(0, n - 2), rob(1, n - 1));
}
```

**Time**: O(n). **Space**: O(1).

