editorial:
**Recurrence**: `dp[i]` = min jumps to land on index `i`. `dp[i] = 1 + min over s in allowed (with i-s >= 0 AND dp[i-s] != Inf) of dp[i-s]`.

**Base**: `dp[0] = 0`. Final answer = `dp[n-1]`, or -1 if Infinity.

```javascript
function variableJumpMinSteps(n, allowed) {
  const target = n - 1;
  if (target === 0) return 0;
  const dp = new Array(n).fill(Infinity);
  dp[0] = 0;
  for (let i = 1; i < n; i++) {
    for (const s of allowed) {
      if (i - s >= 0 && dp[i - s] !== Infinity) {
        dp[i] = Math.min(dp[i], dp[i - s] + 1);
      }
    }
  }
  return dp[target] === Infinity ? -1 : dp[target];
}
```

**Time**: O(n * |allowed|). **Space**: O(n).

This is unbounded-knapsack flavor (each step reusable). For minimum-count problems, basic 1-D DP works perfectly.

