editorial:
**Two parallel DPs**: `len[i]` = length of LIS ending at i; `cnt[i]` = number of distinct LISes ending at i.

**Recurrence**: For each i, scan j < i. If `nums[j] < nums[i]`:
- If `len[j] + 1 > len[i]`: extend; `len[i] = len[j] + 1`, `cnt[i] = cnt[j]`.
- Else if `len[j] + 1 === len[i]`: accumulate; `cnt[i] += cnt[j]`.

**Base**: `len[i] = 1`, `cnt[i] = 1`.

**Final**: `max = max(len)`; answer = `sum(cnt[i] where len[i] === max)`.

```javascript
function numLis(nums) {
  const n = nums.length;
  if (n === 0) return 0;
  const len = new Array(n).fill(1);
  const cnt = new Array(n).fill(1);
  let best = 1;
  for (let i = 1; i < n; i++) {
    for (let j = 0; j < i; j++) {
      if (nums[j] < nums[i]) {
        if (len[j] + 1 > len[i]) {
          len[i] = len[j] + 1;
          cnt[i] = cnt[j];
        } else if (len[j] + 1 === len[i]) {
          cnt[i] += cnt[j];
        }
      }
    }
    if (len[i] > best) best = len[i];
  }
  let total = 0;
  for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) if (len[i] === best) total += cnt[i];
  return total;
}
```

**Time**: O(n^2). **Space**: O(n).

